    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This might be the same issue as jupyter/qtconsole#156. I'm guessing that the problem is that we reset the standard `sys.excepthook` when we're not running user code. It looks like PyQt uses `sys.excepthook` to display exceptions in the event loop, so we should be smarter about that while we're running the PyQt event loop.\n"
